===大氣氧氣的積聚===
<!--{{Main article|Geological history of oxygen}}-->
<!-- CopyEdits Only — DIRECT ALL FUTURE EXPANSION to [[Geological_history_of_oxygen|Geological history of oxygen]] or [[dioxygen_in_biological_reactions|dioxygen in biological reactions]] -->

[[File:Oxygenation-atm.svg|thumb]]

大概在35億年前，地球上出現會進行光合作用的[[古菌|古菌]]和[[細菌|細菌]]。在此之前，[[地球大氣|地球大氣]]中幾乎不存在游離氧氣。到了[[古元古代|古元古代]]，即30至23億年前，地球上第一次出現大量的游離氧氣。<ref name="Crowe2013">{{Cite journal | last1 = Crowe | first1 = S. A. | last2 = Døssing | first2 = L. N. | last3 = Beukes | first3 = N. J. | last4 = Bau | first4 = M. | last5 = Kruger | first5 = S. J. | last6 = Frei | first6 = R. | last7 = Canfield | first7 = D. E. | title = Atmospheric oxygenation three billion years ago | journal = Nature | volume = 501 | issue = 7468 | pages = 535–538 | year = 2013 | pmid = 24067713 | doi = 10.1038/nature12426 }}</ref>地球形成後的首10億年內，游離氧氣會與溶於海洋中的[[鐵|鐵]]結合，形成[[條狀鐵層|條狀鐵層]]。30至27億年前，此類氧氣槽達到飽和，氧氣開始從海洋[[釋氣|釋出]]。17億年前，氧氣水平達到今天的10%。<ref name="Crowe2013" /><ref name="Campbell">{{cite book|last = Campbell|first = Neil A.|last2=Reece|first2=Jane B.|title = Biology|edition = 7th|publisher = Pearson – Benjamin Cummings |date=2005|location = San Francisco|pages = 522–23|isbn = 0-8053-7171-0}}</ref>

24億年前的[[大氧化事件|大氧化事件]]（「氧氣大災難」）期間，海洋和大氣的含氧量大幅上漲，大多數的[[厭氧生物|厭氧生物]]很可能因此絕種。[[好氧生物|好氧生物]]利用<chem>O2</chem>進行[[呼吸作用|呼吸作用]]，可以比厭氧生物產生多許多的[[三磷酸腺苷|ATP]]。<ref name="Freeman">{{cite book|last = Freeman| first = Scott|title = Biological Science, 2nd|publisher = Pearson – Prentice Hall |date=2005|location = Upper Saddle River, NJ|pages = 214, 586|isbn = 0-13-140941-7}}</ref>所有[[真核生物|真核生物]]，包括動植物等複雜多細胞生物，都用<chem>O2</chem>進行呼吸作用。

5.4億年前，地球進入[[寒武紀|寒武紀]]，這段時期的大氣含氧量（依體積）在15%和30%間波動。<ref name="geologic">{{cite journal |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/96/20/10955 |title=Atmospheric oxygen over Phanerozoic time |first=Robert A. |last=Berner |issue=20 |pages=10955–57 |date=1999 |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the USA |pmid=10500106 |doi=10.1073/pnas.96.20.10955 |volume=96 |pmc=34224 |bibcode=1999PNAS...9610955B |author= |access-date=2017-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080307142237/http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/96/20/10955 |archive-date=2008-03-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>約3億年前[[石炭紀|石炭紀]]進入末期時，大氣含氧量達到35%的最高值，<ref name="geologic" />這有可能是當時[[昆蟲|昆蟲]]和[[兩棲類|兩棲類]]動物體型巨大的原因。<ref name=Butterfield2009>{{Cite journal | last1 = Butterfield | first1 = N. J. | title = Oxygen, animals and oceanic ventilation: An alternative view | doi = 10.1111/j.1472-4669.2009.00188.x | journal = Geobiology | volume = 7 | issue = 1 | pages = 1–7 | year = 2009 | pmid = 19200141 | pmc = }}</ref>

含氧量的波動影響遠古氣候：含氧量下降時，大氣密度一同下降，表面蒸發率因而上升，進而提高溫度和降水程度。<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://ns.umich.edu/new/releases/22942-variations-in-atmospheric-oxygen-levels-shaped-earth-s-climate-through-the-ages|doi=10.1126/science.1260670|journal=Science|title=Long-term climate forcing by atmospheric oxygen concentrations|authors=Christopher J. Poulsen, Clay Tabor, Joseph D. White|volume=348|pages=1238–1241|author=|access-date=2017-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713125418/http://ns.umich.edu/new/releases/22942-variations-in-atmospheric-oxygen-levels-shaped-earth-s-climate-through-the-ages|archive-date=2017-07-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>

以目前光合作用的速率，要生成目前整個大氣中所有的氧氣需2千年。<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Natural History of Oxygen|first=Malcolm|last=Dole|url=http://www.jgp.org/cgi/reprint/49/1/5.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=2007-12-16|journal=The Journal of General Physiology|volume=49|pages=5–27|date=1965|doi=10.1085/jgp.49.1.5|pmid=5859927|issue=1|pmc=2195461|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080227014308/http://www.jgp.org/cgi/reprint/49/1/5.pdf|archive-date=2008-02-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==工業生產==
[[File:Hofmann_voltameter_fr.svg|thumb]]]]
{{see also|分餾}}
<!--{{see also|Air separation|Oxygen evolution}}-->

每年從空氣萃取的工業用<chem>O2</chem>有1億噸，萃取方法有二。<ref name="NBB300"/>液態空氣[[分餾法|分餾法]]蒸餾出氮氣，留下液氧，為最常用方法。<ref name="NBB300"/>

另一常用方法主要利用[[沸石|沸石]]做成兩個相同的分子篩。當有不含雜質和水份的空氣通過分子篩時，分子篩會吸收氮氣，讓90%至94%純度的氧氣通過。<ref name="NBB300"/>當其中一個分子篩上的氮氣達到飽和時，可通過降低氣壓或使氧氣反向通過分子篩，使氮氣釋出。兩個分子篩交替吸附、釋放氮氣，達到連續供應氧氣的目的。這種方法稱為{{le|變壓吸附法|pressure swing adsorption}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uigi.com/noncryo.html|title=Non-Cryogenic Air Separation Processes|date=2003|accessdate=2007-12-16|publisher=UIG Inc.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522041406/http://www.uigi.com/noncryo.html|archive-date=2011-05-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>

氧氣可通過電解水來生成。直流電通過水，在正負兩極處會分別形成兩份氫氣和一份氧氣。亦可用電作為催化劑，從氧化物和[[含氧酸|含氧酸]]中萃取氧氣。化學氧氣發生器和氧燭都利用化學催化劑萃取氧氣，應用包括潛水艇維生系統以及客運飛機上突發降壓時的後備維生系統。還有一種生成方法，用高壓或電流使空氣穿過基於[[二氧化鋯|二氧化鋯]]的[[陶瓷|陶瓷]]膜。這樣生成的氧氣有極高的純度。<ref name="NBB301"/>
